e\u0027s even more below. So, at least one more feature video is ahead of us.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if that means the ship is heading to Bop, and when it lands... Something happens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-01T14:01:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow! I don\u0027t think I\u0027ve had my content linked before!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"salaminho","CreatedById":217180,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-01T16:20:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224049692\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635775151\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDone before\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7593204776\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/205421-episode-4s-secret-message/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:171px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlooks like the Kraken to me. But since this is basically a bigger part of the picture we\u0027ve seen last time, suggests that there\u0027s even more below. So, at least one more feature video is ahead of us.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if that means the ship is heading to Bop, and when it lands... Something happens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh thanks! I was looking for a thread with the answer, couldn\u0027t find it. But it was fun deciphering it on my own, learned a few things in the progres.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow it really makes sense, agreed that looks like the kraken.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tkw","CreatedById":142638,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-01T17:05:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice looking planets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-01T20:17:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027ll be the ending of the next video? Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PlutoISaPlanet","CreatedById":206057,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T00:29:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224049899\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635797827\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027ll be the ending of the next video? Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume the vessel is heading somewhere. So it has to make that burn or aproach to said planet/moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T01:17:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224049899\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635797827\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027ll be the ending of the next video? Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelease date?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T12:54:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw something that we\u0027d expect the next video in March or April.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T14:41:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050142\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635857683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw something that we\u0027d expect the next video in March or April.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T14:55:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it was in the place where the video was posted by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196459-coolranchaj/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022196459\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196459-coolranchaj/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@CoolRanchAJ\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MARL_Mk1","CreatedById":192535,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-02T17:00:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, Spring 2022 new Feature Episode with either a release date on Fall 2022 or a light-hearted delay announcement for 2023.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nGive us some specific information already, jfc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SciMan","CreatedById":12748,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T17:59:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, since we\u0027re talking so much about seeing stars in the sky, I have a question. Do you think the stars we\u0027ll actually be able to visit will be clearly visible in the skybox? I would hope that they are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdditionally, I hope that the stars that the other planetary systems are orbiting are not the same \u0022generic Sun type\u0022 aka G type star that Kerbol appears to be.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIdeally I\u0027d like to see all types of stars represented, but since we\u0027re not getting enough \u0022other stars\u0022 to visit to cover all those types, I\u0027d like to see a Type M (red dwarf stars that are lower mass, cooler, and have a much longer life than our G-type Sun that Earth orbits), and a Type A B or O star (\u0022white\u0022 or \u0022blue\u0022 stars, hotter and more massive and shorter lived than our G-type Sun that Earth orbits).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust some acknowledgement that not all stars are like our Sun is what I\u0027m looking for, and if KSP 2 gets DLC that is \u0022more star systems\u0022 along with probably some new rocket parts, then hopefully we\u0027ll be able to see even more kinds of stars, perhaps even exotic ones like white dwarfs, neutron stars, and maybe even a stellar-mass black hole (solar panels won\u0027t work well at all around that last one unless it\u0027s a binary system with a black hole feeding on something like a red giant).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf things are too far along in development for this kind of idea to be implemented, it\u0027s my hope that it will be relatively easy for mods to add such things into the game (including the fact that the light from said other types of star would make all the paint colors of our rockets render differently, not sure how hard that is to accomplish tho).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-03T18:01:35Z\u0022 title=\u002211/03/2021 06:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 3, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by SciMan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T18:10:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe stars still won\u0027t be much more than a dot in the sky, among many others that are a part of the skybox itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I assume if you zoom out enough to see a local neighborhood, you\u0027d be able to tell where they are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SunlitZelkova","CreatedById":206402,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T20:45:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635963038\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe stars still won\u0027t be much more than a dot in the sky, among many others that are a part of the skybox itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on the distance of the star, couldn\u0027t it be visible during twilight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635962356\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212748\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SciMan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, SciMan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, since we\u0027re talking so much about seeing stars in the sky, I have a question. Do you think the stars we\u0027ll actually be able to visit will be clearly visible in the skybox? I would hope that they are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be cool if the same could happen for planets too. Seeing Jool glow in the evening sky would be really nice while driving around the space center.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T21:32:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635972301\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206402\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SunlitZelkova\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, SunlitZelkova said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be cool if the same could happen for planets too. Seeing Jool glow in the evening sky would be really nice while driving around the space center\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProblem\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003Ewith KSP is that most, probably all planets are technically rendered all the time, but smaller than a pixel, so you can\u0027t see them. Notice how Minmus is like 3 pixels wide from the surface of Kerbin? And I believe you can\u0027t even see Gilly from Eve.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EKsp2 could fix that by adding some reflective material to, what they call it, scaled space? of the planets far far away (forgive me messing up technical speak), so\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eyou could technically see a bright point in the sky, that unfortunately wouldn\u0027t be a planet, only a texture, but that\u0027s about it. If needed, I dunno.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635972301\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206402\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SunlitZelkova\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, SunlitZelkova said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on the distance of the star, couldn\u0027t it be visible during twilight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparent magnitude* You can\u0027t really see Proxima Centauri even though it\u0027s the closest star. You can technically see Sirius with perfect conditions even before sunset, but it\u0027s still a dot, despite it being only 8ly away from Earth. Well, at least until you pull out a powerful equipment (example: Betelgeuse), but for the naked eye, every celestial body except for the sun and the moon are just flickering points. And I don\u0027t expect it to be any different in the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}